 Responsible Social Media Use – Checklist for College Students

 ✅ Do's
- Think before you post; ensure your content is respectful and appropriate.
- Maintain a professional profile, especially on platforms like LinkedIn.
- Verify information before sharing to avoid spreading misinformation.
- Use strong privacy settings to control who can view your content.
- Be respectful in comments and discussions, even when you disagree.

❌ Don'ts
- Do not share sensitive personal information (address, phone number, ID details).
- Avoid posting offensive, abusive, or discriminatory content.
- Do not engage in cyberbullying or trolling.
- Avoid oversharing about your personal life or daily activities.
- Do not click on suspicious links or accept requests from unknown people.
